events.originalText: An earthquake registering 7.0 Mw struck Haiti, killing more than 100,000 people.
events.subtitle: 2010 Haiti earthquake
events.headline: Earthquake in Haiti kills over 100,000 people

events.originalText: Iranian physicist Massoud Ali-Mohammadi was assassinated while leaving his home for the University of Tehran, where he was a professor.
events.subtitle: Massoud Ali-Mohammadi
events.headline: Iranian physicist Massoud Ali-Mohammadi assassinated

events.originalText: Comet McNaught (pictured) reached perihelion, becoming the brightest comet in over 40 years, with an apparent magnitude of −5.5.
events.subtitle: Comet McNaught
events.headline: Comet McNaught becomes brightest comet in 40 years

events.originalText: British rock band Led Zeppelin released their first album, Led Zeppelin, in the United States.
events.subtitle: Rock music
events.headline: Led Zeppelin releases first album in the United States

events.originalText: Seventy-three-year-old psychology professor James Bedford became the first person to be cryonically preserved with intent of future resuscitation.
events.subtitle: James Bedford
events.headline: James Bedford cryonically preserved for future resuscitation

events.originalText: Sultan Jamshid bin Abdullah was overthrown by rebels led by John Okello, ending 200 years of Arab dominance in Zanzibar.
events.subtitle: Jamshid bin Abdullah of Zanzibar
events.headline: Rebels led by John Okello overthrow Sultan Jamshid bin Abdullah in Zanzibar

events.originalText: An underground explosion at a coal mine in Staffordshire, England, killed 155 men and boys.
events.subtitle: Minnie Pit Disaster
events.headline: Underground explosion in coal mine in England kills 155

events.originalText: Oswald Boelcke and Max Immelmann became the first German aviators to be awarded the Pour le Mérite, Germany's highest military honour.
events.subtitle: Oswald Boelcke
events.headline: Oswald Boelcke and Max Immelmann awarded Germany's highest military honour

events.originalText: During a storm, the crew of Lynmouth Lifeboat Station transported their 10-ton lifeboat 15 mi (24 km) overland in order to rescue a damaged schooner.
events.subtitle: Lynmouth Lifeboat Station
events.headline: Lynmouth Lifeboat Station crew transports lifeboat overland to rescue schooner

events.originalText: The National Trust for Places of Historic Interest or Natural Beauty, a conservation organisation in England, Wales and Northern Ireland, was founded.
events.subtitle: National Trust
events.headline: National Trust for Places of Historic Interest founded in England, Wales, and Northern Ireland

events.originalText: Anglo-Zulu War: Natal Native Contingent and British troops defeated Zulu forces in the Action at Sihayo's Kraal.
events.subtitle: Anglo-Zulu War
events.headline: Natal Native Contingent and British troops defeat Zulu forces in Action at Sihayo's Kraal

events.originalText: The foundation stone of Saint Fin Barre's Cathedral in Cork was laid.
events.subtitle: Saint Fin Barre's Cathedral
events.headline: Foundation stone laid for Saint Fin Barre's Cathedral in Cork

events.originalText: John Rennie's scheme to defend St Mary's Church in Reculver from coastal erosion was abandoned in favour of demolition, despite the church being an exemplar of Anglo-Saxon architecture.
events.subtitle: John Rennie the Elder
events.headline: Scheme to defend St Mary's Church in Reculver abandoned in favor of demolition

events.originalText: Mission Santa Clara de Asís (pictured), a Spanish mission in California that formed the basis of both the city of Santa Clara and Santa Clara University, was established by the Franciscans.
events.subtitle: Mission Santa Clara de Asís
events.headline: Mission Santa Clara de Asís established in California

events.originalText: The fort at Allahabad was surrendered to the forces of Mughal emperor Aurangzeb.
events.subtitle: Allahabad Fort
events.headline: Fort at Allahabad surrendered to forces of Mughal emperor Aurangzeb

events.originalText: Bayinnaung, who later assembled what was probably the largest empire in the history of mainland Southeast Asia, was crowned as the king of the Burmese Toungoo dynasty.
events.subtitle: Bayinnaung
events.headline: Bayinnaung crowned king of the Burmese Toungoo dynasty

events.originalText: Basiliscus became Byzantine emperor after Zeno was forced to flee Constantinople.
events.subtitle: Basiliscus
events.headline: Basiliscus becomes Byzantine emperor after Zeno flees Constantinople
